5050|HISTORY OF THE LIBRARY OF GRAZ TECHNICAL UNIVERSITY 1875|-1975|.PART 1| OF AN ARTICLE ON THE HISTORY OF THE LIBRARY AT GRAZ TECHNICALUNIVERSITY. THE FOUNDATIONS FOR A TECHNICAL UNIVERSITY WERE LAID IN 1811| WHENARCHDUKE JOHANN REALISED HIS PLANS FOR A SCIENTIFIC INSTITUTION AND DONATEDHIS PRIVATE COLLECTION, INCLUDING BOOKS, TO THE PROVINCE OF STEIERMARK, BUT ITDID NOT BECOME A STATE INSTITUTION UNTIL 1874| AND A LIBRARY, WITH ITS OWNBUILDING, BUDGET AND STAFF, WAS NOT ESTABLISHED UNTIL 1889|. THE RELATIONSHIPBETWEEN THE ACADEMIC STAFF AND THE LIBRARY WAS ALWAYS FRAUGHT WITHDIFFICULTIES AND FULL INDEPENDENCE FOR THE LIBRARY WAS NOT ACHIEVED UNTIL1960|. BRIEF BIOGRAPHIES OF THE 8| LIBRARY DIRECTORS TO DATE AND A REVIEW OFSTAFFING AND BUDGETS UP TO 1975| ARE INCLUDED.
