5077|ADJUSTED AGE DISTRIBUTION AND ITS APPLICATION TO IMPACT FACTOR AND IMMEDIACYINDEX.FOR THE AGE COUNT BETWEEN CITING AND CITED PAPERS, THE DIFFERENCE IN THE YEAROF PUBLICATION IS WIDELY USED. IN SOME CASES, THE FREQUENCY OBTAINED ISINACCURATE BECAUSE OF AGE BIAS. DESCRIBES A PROBABILISTIC METHOD FOR ADJUSTINGTHE RAW FREQUENCY, AND ITS APPLICATION TO THE IMPACT FACTOR AND IMMEDIACYINDEX IN JOURNAL EVALUATION. THE MAIN PROCEDURE IS THAT &B OF THE RAWFREQUENCY AT ANY GIVEN AGE IS ASSIGNED TO THE PREVIOUS AGE AND TO THEFOLLOWING AGE, RESPECTIVELY. ADJUSTING THE FREQUENCY OVER ALL AGES OF USE, THECURVE REPRESENTING THE AGE DISTRIBUTION BECOMES SMOOTHER.
