5170|LIBRARY STAFF DEVELOPMENT COURSE.BASED ON A PAPER PRESENTED 14| JUNE 78| AT THE 78|TH ANNUAL MEETING OF THEMEDICAL LIBRARY ASSOCIATION, CHICAGO, ILLINOIS. DESCRIBES THE STAFFDEVELOPMENT PROGRAMME OPERATED BY THE MOODY MEDICAL LIBRARY AT THE UNIVERSITYOF TEXAS. THE PROGRAMME'S PURPOSE IS TO PROVIDE CONTINUING EDUCATION FOR THELIBRARY STAFF WHILE CONCURRENTLY' (1|) PROVIDING INFORMATION CONCERNINGSPECIFIC LIBRARY SERVICES AND PROGRAMMES; (2|) ILLUSTRATING THEINTERRELATIONSHIPS OF THE DEPARTMENTS AND DIVISIONS WITHIN THE LIBRARY; (3|)DEVELOPING A SENSE OF TEAMWORK AND LOYALTY; AND (4|) DEVELOPING JOB PRIDE.INCLUDES THE FORM USED TO EVALUATE THE EFFICIENCY OF THE PROGRAMME'S VARIOUSCOMPONENTS.
